Head of Governance & Compliance
Charterhouse
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 6 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
A leading UAE Property Developer who has been responsible for a number of prodigious developments throughout Dubai is looking to hire a Head of Governance & Compliance to join their rapidly expanding business.
You will be responsible for reviewing, changing and implementing all governance processes at group level. You will deliver a Corporate Governance Manual into processes and activities delivering the appropriate governance of planning, processing and decision making activity at group level.
In addition you will be responsible for the overall leadership of the compliance team overseeing the adherence laws, regulations, standards and best practice ensuring that adequate compliance checks are in place for approving new applications.
REQUIREMENTS
The successful candidate should be a qualified lawyer with 8yrs+ PQE and a strong governance background in the UAE. You should have strong analytical skills including the ability to think critically and logically; creative problem solving and excellent decision-making skills.
ABOUT THE COMPANY
During the last ten years, Charterhouse has been operating across Dubai, Abu Dhabi and the GCC Markets. In many ways, we were the recruiter who established and set the standards within the regional recruitment industry benchmarking and innovating the service levels associated to Search and Selection.
Charterhouse understands the dynamics attached to talent acquisition, relationship management and the required service levels within the regional industry. Our heritage is now our main strength as we continue to work within our core markets to deliver key account management and strong contingency recruitment practices to our clients and candidates.
